lead_paragraph: Early results showed the governing party, United Russia, with 46 percent of the vote in an election marked by low turnout in large cities.

byline.contributor: Oleg Matsnev and Sophia Kishkovsky contributed reporting.

headline.print_headline: Parties Backing Putin Make a Strong Showing in Elections
headline.main: Pro-Putin Parties Show Strength in Russian Parliament Elections

snippet: Early results showed the governing party, United Russia, with 46 percent of the vote in an election marked by low turnout in large cities....
abstract: Early results in Russia's election shows Pres Vladimir Putin's United Russia party and its allies maintaining lock on Parliament; corruption in past elections has led to widespread voter malaise and particularly low voter turnout in cities.
